ing situation in the Country and will make Official pronouncement on the Examinations if the need arises” It stated. Azeez added that only the 2020 National Common Entrance (NCEE)  was postponed indefinitely due to the outbreak of COVID-19 while other dates remain the same for now. vanguard The National Examinations Council (NECO) has called on the Nigerian Government to formulate policies aimed at promoting discipline and honesty among teachers, school administrators and students. The acting Registrar of the council, Mr Abubakar Gana, made this known in a brief submitted to the Minister of Education, Malam Adamu Adamu… October 8, 2019 In "Education" Some candidates of the National Examination Council (NECO), who could not write some papers due to the recent Plateau killings in the state have pleaded with the council to re-conduct the examinations. July 19, 2018 In "News" ABUJA- THE National Examinations Council, NECO, has urged the Federal Government to formulate a deliberate policy aimed at promoting discipline and a culture of honesty among teachers, school administrators and students. October 9, 2019 In "News"